f life. His worldview grew more audacious, his confidence in the magical power of the word grew more assured. Drowning in 1901 at 23, Konevskoi left a legacy unfinished, rich, and intriguing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aPoets, Russiany19th centuryvBiography. 0aSymbolism (Literary movement)zRussia. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618117014zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618117014.jpg  a978-3-11-068814-6 ASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015c2008d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA